        "content": "Social media companies routinely collect and exploit vast amounts of personal data without adequate user consent or understanding. They track user behavior, preferences, and even sensitive information, often sharing it with third parties or using it for targeted advertising. This not only breaches user privacy but also leaves individuals vulnerable to data breaches and misuse. Current regulations are insufficient to protect user rights, necessitating stricter laws that enforce transparency, limit data collection, and prioritize user consent, ensuring that privacy is not sacrificed for profit. Users deserve to have control over their own data and how it is used.",
